a psychology of learning basic.wthis paper addresses the question: what does a person knowfollowing learning of basic programming?  several underlying conceptualstructures are identified: () a transaction is an event thatoccurs in the computer and involves some operation on some objectat some location, () a prestatement is a set of transactions correspondingto a line of code, () chunks are frequently occurring configurations of prestatements corresponding to several lines of code.cacm november, mayer, r.e..kbasic, learning, instruction.c. . .ca db january ,   : am